 origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":70,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":79,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":114,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"William Marney was born in Essex, England as the son of Father of William Marney No more info and Mother of William Marney No more info. He married Agnes de Cocton after February 1236. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1263, in his hometown."},"et":{"–alive 1263":"–1263","–1263":"–1263","1196–1236":"1196–1236","1277–Male":"1277–Surnud","1279–Male":"1279–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","alive 1263":"1263","aft 1236   2nd husband":"pärast veebruari 1236","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","1224":"1224","1279":"1279","1277":"1277","1263":"1263","1196":"1196","Coughton, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fi":{"–alive 1263":"–1263","–1263":"–1263","1196–1236":"1196–1236","1277–Male":"1277–Kuollut","1279–Male":"1279–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","alive 1263":"1263","aft 1236   2nd husband":"helmikuu 1236 jälkeen","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","1224":"1224","1279":"1279","1277":"1277","1263":"1263","1196":"1196","Coughton, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, England","Essex, England":"Essex, England"},"fr":{"–alive 1263":"–1263","–1263":"–1263","1196–1236":"1196–1236","1277–Male":"1277–Décédé","1279–Male":"1279–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","alive 1263":"1263","aft 1236   2nd husband":"après février 1236","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","1224":"1224","1279":"1279","1277":"1277","1263":"1263","1196":"1196","Coughton, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, Angleterre","Essex, England":"Essex, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"William Marney est né à Essex, Angleterre, fils de Father of William Marney No more info et Mother of William Marney No more info. Il a épousé Agnes de Cocton après février 1236. Ils ont eu au moins 2 fils. Il est décédé en 1263, dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"–alive 1263":"–1263","–1263":"–1263","1196–1236":"1196–1236","1277–Male":"1277–Verstorben","1279–Male":"1279–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","alive 1263":"1263","aft 1236   2nd husband":"nach Februar 1236","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1236":"1236","1224":"1224","1279":"1279","1277":"1277","1263":"1263","1196":"1196","Coughton, War